    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Claparède</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 11th ultimo, asking the protection of the United States
                    minister to Brazil for the estate of the deceased Swiss citizen Lecoultre, and
                    for the person of its manager, Jean Etter, also a Swiss citizen.</p>
                <p>Under the conditions described by you, the estate belonging to a Swiss citizen,
                    and the resident manager, Jean Etter, being also a Swiss, I will, have pleasure
                    in instructing Mr. Thompson, the United States minister at Bio de Janeiro, to
                    use his good offices within proper limits for their friendly protection in case
                    of need, in view of the absence of a diplomatic representative of Switzerland in
                    Brazil, and with the consent of the Brazilian Government.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
